The escape sequences
\f3\e\e\f1,
\f3\e\^.\f1,
\f3\e"\f1,
\f3\e$\f1,
\f3\e\(**\f1,
\f3\ea\f1,
\f3\en\f1,
\f3\et\f1,
and
\f3\e\f1(newline) are interpreted in \f2copy mode\f1 (\(sc7.2).
